data.body:
Right now, running all of Atom against a different package API (for local development on the API within the Atom core team, or for future users that want to run against some kind of API-compatible alternate package index or mirror inside their firewall) is not super straightforward. `apm` will do the right thing with an env var, but if you [search the org](https://github.com/search?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=org%3Aatom+%22atom.io%2Fapi%22&type=Code&ref=searchresults) you'll see it's hardcoded in more than a few places.

We should add a core config setting, env var override, or something that can be set in the console to provide the api root URL, and then update all packages to use it.

@atom/feedback
